name: SPARC: ELF Symbol Table Entry: Register Symbol

rows.Meaning:
Index into the string table for
the name of the symbol, or the value 0 for a scratch
register.
Register number. See the ABI manual for integer register assignments.

Bind is
typically STB_GLOBAL, type must be STT_SPARC_REGISTER.

SHN_ABS if this object initializes this
register symbol,SHN_UNDEF otherwise.

rows.Name: SYMINFO_BT_PARENT
rows.Meaning: Symbol bound to parent. The parent is the first object to cause this dynamic object to be loaded.

rows.Name: SYMINFO_BT_NONE
rows.Meaning: Symbol has no special symbol binding.

rows.Name: SYMINFO_FLG_DIRECT
rows.Meaning: Symbol reference has a direct association to the object containing the definition.

rows.Name: SYMINFO_FLG_FILTER
rows.Meaning: Symbol definition acts as a standard filter.

rows.Name: SYMINFO_FLG_COPY
rows.Meaning: Symbol definition is the result of a copy-relocation.

rows.Name: SYMINFO_FLG_LAZYLOAD
rows.Meaning: Symbol reference is to an object that should be lazily loaded.

rows.Name: SYMINFO_FLG_DIRECTBIND
rows.Meaning: Symbol reference should be bound directly to the definition.

rows.Name: SYMINFO_FLG_NOEXTDIRECT
rows.Meaning: Do not allow an external reference to directly bind to this symbol definition.

rows.Name: SYMINFO_FLG_AUXILIARY
rows.Meaning: Symbol definition acts as an auxiliary filter.

rows.Name: SYMINFO_FLG_INTERPOSE
rows.Meaning: Symbol definition acts as an interposer. This attribute is only applicable for dynamic executables.

rows.Name: SYMINFO_FLG_DEFERRED
rows.Meaning: Symbol should not be included in BIND_NOW relocations.

rows.Name: VER_FLG_INFO
rows.Meaning: SHT_SUNW_versym reference exists for informational purposes, and need not be validated at runtime.

rows.Name: VER_NDX_GLOBAL
rows.Meaning:
Symbol has global scope and is assigned to
the base version definition.

Symbol has global scope and is assigned to a
user-defined version definition, SHT_SUNW_verdef, or a version dependency, SHT_SUNW_verneed.
